history.text: Hi there. Have you seen the Wolf of Wall Street?
Yes, have you?
No but it sounds interesting.
I think it is very close to what actually goes on on Wall Street. It seems like such a high stress job, and they portray that well in the movie in my opinion
It's suppose to be a comedy.  Is  it very funny?
I don't think it was a comedy at all. Some of it was funny because of the people that are playing the characters though.
I'm a big fan of some the actors in the movie.  I love Jonah Hill and Matthew McConaughey.
Oh, yeah. Matthew McConaughey was great. He has a scene where he explains the Wall Street chest thump. Haha!
Doesn't seem like the critics liked it very much though.
Yeah, and I don't understand what they mean by "black comedy"? Black as in the race of people? Or black as in a "dark" comedy?
I am assuming as in "dark".  I often disagree with critcs about movies so I am not discouraged.
Yeah, I think so too.  I also generally disagree with the critics too.
I see it has Leonardo DiCaprio also.
Yes, it does. I generally like movies with him in it.
Yes DiCaprio and McConaughey. You can't go wrong.
I don't think so either!
It sounds intense.  I really need to see this movie.

They portray such a wild culture of the people "of Wall Street". I wonder if it is really like that. I know I mentioned earlier that I think it is, but I don't know. I sometimes feel like things are greatly exaggerated in movies.
Yeah, you really should!
If Wall Street is like this then WoW!!!
I think Scorsese did a great job directing this movie. There are so many things that catch your eye, lol.
HAHAHA! Yeah, right?!
It's definitely on my list of must movies.  Scorsese is an amazing director.
Stockbrokers, sex, drugs.... Sounds like a soap opera

I think it sounds pretty legitimate. I mean, even people that don't have all that money are into sex and drugs almost obsessively, if not completely so. Sex and drugs, unfortunately, make the world go around. Oh, and money!
It really is like an elongated soap in a way.
I'm sure it ends in arrests and downfalls.  Just like Wallstreet!!!
The mentor flaunts money at him and then gets him with drugs and women.
This will be added to my list of must sees!!
Yeah, lmao! Nothing good comes of that life style. Probably death. Nothing gory or anything in this movie. Just realistic, I think. No matter how sad that may be!
Fun movie to watch though.
